---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/cca-partners.css';
const html = `


  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="crumb">
        <a href="/">Innovia</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span style="color:#fff;">CCA Global Partners</span>
        <div class="right">
          <span class="dot"></span>
          The cooperative behind Innovia &middot; member co-op since <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[year]</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="title-row">
        <h1>
          A cooperative of <em>cooperatives.</em>
        </h1>
        <div class="meta-stack">
          <div class="ind">CCA Global Partners</div>
          <p>Innovia operates inside CCA Global Partners &mdash; one of the largest privately held cooperatives in North America, and the structural reason an independent CAM company in our membership gets pricing terms that should only exist at national scale.</p>
          <div class="ind">Profile &middot; <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[updated]</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ORG PROFILE BAND -->
      <div class="org-band">
        <div class="logo-frame">
          <div class="logo-mark">CCA<span class="lo">Logo placeholder</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="org-body">
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Established</span>
            <span class="v placeholder placeholder-inline">[year]</span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Headquartered</span>
            <span class="v placeholder placeholder-inline">Manchester, NH</span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Member co-ops</span>
            <span class="v placeholder placeholder-inline">[#]</span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Industries served</span>
            <span class="v">Flooring &middot; Lighting &middot; Bicycle &middot; Travel &middot; Hospitality &middot; <span class="green-text">Community Mgmt.</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Combined member companies</span>
            <span class="v placeholder placeholder-inline">[#,###]+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-row">
            <span class="k">Annual member sales volume</span>
            <span class="v placeholder placeholder-inline">$[##]B+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="org-tagline">
            <span class="t-label">Stance</span>
            <p>Member-owned, member-governed. No outside investors. No public stock. The cooperative serves the operators, not the other way around.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NARRATIVE -->
  <section class="narrative">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="layout">
        <aside class="left">
          <div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">No. 01</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>The relationship</div>
          <h2>How Innovia <em>fits.</em></h2>
          <nav class="toc">
            <a href="#chapter-1"><span class="num">01</span> A coop of coops</a>
            <a href="#chapter-2"><span class="num">02</span> Why CAM joined</a>
            <a href="#chapter-3"><span class="num">03</span> What it unlocks</a>
            <a href="#sister-coops"><span class="num">04</span> Sister cooperatives</a>
          </nav>
        </aside>
        <div class="body">
          <p id="chapter-1">
            <strong>CCA Global Partners</strong> is one of the largest privately held cooperatives in North America. It is not a holding company. It is not a franchise. It is a federation of <em>industry-specific cooperatives</em>, each owned by the independent operators it serves &mdash; flooring retailers, lighting showrooms, bicycle dealers, hoteliers, travel agencies, and, with the addition of Innovia, community association management firms.
          </p>
          <p>
            Each member co-op runs its own admissions, governance, and program for its industry. CCA at the top is the engine that makes the whole thing leverage: shared back-office infrastructure, consolidated banking and treasury, captive insurance capacity, technology partnerships, and a board that has been running cooperatives at this scale since <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[founding decade]</span>.
          </p>

          <h3 id="chapter-2">Why an HOA-industry co-op joined</h3>
          <p>
            <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Brodsky and Greenberg]</span> didn&rsquo;t build Innovia inside CCA by accident. Two things drew the founding members in. First, the structural fit: CCA was already the country&rsquo;s best example of a federation of industry cooperatives running successfully against consolidated capital. Second, the back-end leverage: CCA&rsquo;s scale meant Innovia&rsquo;s first vendor program could open with banking and treasury terms no independent CAM firm had ever seen.
          </p>
          <p class="pull">
            Joining CCA didn&rsquo;t make Innovia bigger. It made every member firm bigger, the day they joined.
            <cite>&mdash; <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Brodsky]</span>, on the CCA decision</cite>
          </p>

          <h3 id="chapter-3">What it unlocks for our members</h3>
          <p>
            Concretely: Innovia members can access the same pricing structures available across the CCA membership where it overlaps the CAM line items &mdash; banking, treasury, captive insurance capacity, technology partnerships, and shared services. They run their companies independently, draft their own engagement letters, and serve their own boards &mdash; and they do it on the back of a vendor program negotiated across <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[#,###]+</span> member companies in <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[#]</span> industries.
          </p>
          <p>
            None of that requires giving up a CAM owner&rsquo;s independence. The whole point of the federation is that it doesn&rsquo;t.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LEVERAGE GRID -->
  <section class="leverage">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow on-dark"><span class="num" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5)">No. 02</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>The leverage that comes with it</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 14px;">What an Innovia member gets, by way of <em>the federation.</em></h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          Six categories where the CCA umbrella materially changes the terms an independent CAM firm operates under. Detailed terms live in the member portal; the structure is below.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="lev-grid">
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">01</div><h4>Banking &amp; treasury</h4><p>Operating, reserve, and association banking terms negotiated at federation scale. Treasury yields and deposit terms member firms can&rsquo;t replicate alone.</p><span class="meta">CCA-wide &middot; multi-bank</span></article>
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">02</div><h4>Captive insurance capacity</h4><p>Access to CCA-affiliated captive structures for property, GL, D&amp;O, and cyber lines &mdash; underwriting capacity that survived the recent hard market.</p><span class="meta">CCA-affiliated captive</span></article>
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">03</div><h4>Technology partnerships</h4><p>Software vendor terms negotiated across the federation &mdash; AMS, accounting, AI tooling, call-center infrastructure, communications.</p><span class="meta">Multi-co-op leverage</span></article>
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">04</div><h4>Shared back-office</h4><p>HR infrastructure, payroll, benefits, retirement plans, training programs &mdash; the kind of operating spine a national has built in, available to independents.</p><span class="meta">CCA shared services</span></article>
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">05</div><h4>Cooperative finance</h4><p>Working capital and acquisition finance structures designed for cooperative member firms, not private-equity roll-ups.</p><span class="meta">Member-friendly terms</span></article>
        <article class="lev-card"><div class="num">06</div><h4>Governance infrastructure</h4><p>A board, an audit, and the cooperative-law experience to run an industry co-op without re-inventing the legal scaffolding from scratch.</p><span class="meta">Governance &middot; legal</span></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SISTER CO-OPS -->
  <section class="sisters" id="sister-coops">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">No. 03</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>Sister cooperatives</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 14px;">The other industries <em>inside the federation.</em></h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          Each CCA member cooperative serves a different industry but runs on the same principle: independent operators pooling buying power, sharing intelligence, and keeping their independence. Innovia is the federation&rsquo;s entry into community association management.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="sister-grid">
        <article class="sister"><div class="logo placeholder placeholder-inline">[Logo]</div><h4 class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Sister co-op 01]</h4><p class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Industry &middot; member-companies served &middot; one-line description.]</p></article>
        <article class="sister"><div class="logo placeholder placeholder-inline">[Logo]</div><h4 class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Sister co-op 02]</h4><p class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Industry &middot; one-line description.]</p></article>
        <article class="sister"><div class="logo placeholder placeholder-inline">[Logo]</div><h4 class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Sister co-op 03]</h4><p class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Industry &middot; one-line description.]</p></article>
        <article class="sister"><div class="logo placeholder placeholder-inline">[Logo]</div><h4 class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Sister co-op 04]</h4><p class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Industry &middot; one-line description.]</p></article>
        <article class="sister highlight"><div class="logo"><img src="/assets/logos/innovia-white-green.png" alt="Innovia Co-op"></div><h4>Innovia Co-op</h4><p>Community association management. <span>80+</span> member firms across <span>25+</span> states.</p></article>
        <article class="sister"><div class="logo placeholder placeholder-inline">[Logo]</div><h4 class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Sister co-op 06]</h4><p class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Industry &middot; one-line description.]</p></article>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-note">
        <span class="k">Note</span>
        <p>Logos, founding years, and member-company counts for each sister cooperative will be sourced from CCA before publication. Treat the lockup above as a structural placeholder.</p>
        <a href="https://www.ccaglobalpartners.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit ccaglobalpartners.com &nbsp;&rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CREED -->
  <section class="creed">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">
        <span class="bar"></span>
        Inside the federation
        <span class="bar"></span>
      </div>
      <blockquote>
        A federation of operators is what <em>independence</em> looks like <em>at scale.</em>
      </blockquote>
      <cite>
        &mdash; The CCA model, in shorthand
      </cite>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-finale">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="frame">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--innovia-navy); opacity: 0.65;"><span class="num" style="color: var(--innovia-navy);">No. 04</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>Join the room</div>
          <h2>Independent operators. <em>Federation</em> leverage.</h2>
          <p class="lead">If you run an independent CAM firm and you want the back-end leverage of a federation while keeping the brand, the engagement letters, and the boards you serve, this is the conversation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="actions">
          <a href="/for-cams/why-innovia/" class="btn btn-navy">
            Why Innovia for your firm
            <svg class="arrow" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m13 6 6 6-6 6"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/schedule-a-conversation/" class="btn btn-outline">Schedule a Conversation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  


  
`;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About CCA Global Partners · Innovia Co-op"
  description="About CCA Global Partners · Innovia Co-op"
  ogImage="/assets/og/option-1-type-led.png"
  activeNav="about"
  ctaLabel="Schedule a Conversation"
  ctaHref="/schedule-a-conversation/"
>
  <Fragment set:html={html} />
</BaseLayout>
